        "#**Phase 1 - Business Understanding**\n",
        "\n",
        "Introduction\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "Heart disease is a major cause of death worldwide, and traditional diagnostic\n",
        "methods can be slow and unreliable, which will lead to delays in treatment. This is challenging in areas with limited access to specialized healthcare resources. Through analysis of large datasets, machine learning (ML) could provide a viable approach for early diagnosis by identifying the key risk factors and improving the early prediction for heart disease. This project aims to identify the most significant health indicators of heart disease risk, enhance prediction accuracy to improve patient outcomes, and reduce healthcare burdens.\n",
        "\n",
        "Problem Statement\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "*   Traditional diagnostics rely on physical exams, medical history, and biological tests, which are slow and subjective.\n",
        "*   Current Machine Learning approaches are limited by small, unrepresentative datasets, reducing generalizability to broader population.\n",
        "*   Our study uses a reasonably sized dataset to advance Machine Learning, improving prediction accuracy and broader applicability.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "Objectives\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "1.   To identify key health indicators that significantly influence cardiovascular disease, providing information into the most impactful factors for early detection.\n",
        "2.   To develop machine learning algorithms that analyses health indicators for accurate cardiovascular disease prediction.\n",
        "3.   To evaluate and compare the best machine learning algorithms in enhancing the accuracy of cardiovascular disease prediction.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
